- Centralized Grist metadata handling by describing rich column info, the shared label map, and the helper that translates friendly keys to column IDs before any network call (`scripts/grist/infra/relay.ts:14-150`). This guarantees consistent lookups for both reads and mutations regardless of how Grist names/renames the underlying columns.
- Reworked `getAllGristRows` to rely on the resolved column IDs so the data normalization step no longer depends on raw label strings and gracefully handles missing columns (`scripts/grist/infra/relay.ts:151-190`).
- Added two exported helpers: `updateRow(rowId, { description, status, done })` performs a PATCH against the table and `insertRow({ project, item, ... })` POSTs a new record after mapping the provided fields to column IDs (`scripts/grist/infra/relay.ts:192-264`). Both functions validate inputs, reuse the cached table metadata, and bubble up clear errors if Grist rejects the request.

**How to use**
```ts
import { updateRow, insertRow } from "./infra/relay";

await updateRow(3, {
  description: "ÏÑ§Î™Ö ÏóÖÎç∞Ïù¥Ìä∏",
  status: "ÏßÑÌñâÏ§ë",
  done: false,
});

await insertRow({
  project: "Ïã†Í∑ú ÌîÑÎ°úÏ†ùÌä∏",
  item: "Ìï† Ïùº",
  description: "ÏûêÎèô ÏÉùÏÑ±",
  status: "ÎåÄÍ∏∞",
  done: false,
});
```

These helpers share the same env/config bootstrapping as the existing query flow, so you can call them anywhere after `initGristConfig()`.

